more nightmares please help me lately i have been having re occuring nightmares that my uncle who raped me when i was nine years old was on the news for raping a bunch of other girls my picture was one of the pictures on there the news came on when my cousin my mom and my grandma was in the room then i ran and locked myself in a room because i was terrified mortified that they found out b c no one knew i wouldnt talk to anyone for a long time anyways now whether i am asleep or not everytime i close my eyes even for a minute i see my uncles face very clearly i have had lots of nightmares about the rape reliving it but this nightmare just starting occuring how can i make it stop please help i am pretty sure that i have ptsd but i just want to know how to stop this thanks in advance also does anyone know why these nightmares could have started any advice would be great no i am not on any medications i have started taking muscle relaxors and some other kinds of meds but that is not what caused it b c they started shortly before i started taking them if anyone can talk and has aim please add me jbrinkley hi it sounds like you are suffering from flashbacks which can happen when awake or asleep when your asleep its classed as a nightmare when you feel a flashback coming on try to ground yourself by touching something that will bring you to the present keep telling yourself it was in the past he cant hurt me now when you awake from a nightmare touch a teddy or your bed and remind yourself that it was only a nightmare it happened but its not happening now try learning a list that could help you to ground yourself for example say your name where you live how old you are name objects in the room your in or that are around you there is support out there for you this website is for survivors of abuse and rape and can help you alot with ptsd flashbacks and memories hope this helps Post-traumatic stress disorder Traumatic incident reduction Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Miss Saigon 